text: Marie-Josephe Jean-Pierre (born 1 May 1975) is a Mauritian badminton player. She competed in three events at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1975 births Category:Living people Category:Mauritian female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of Mauritius Category:Badminton players at the 1996 Summer Olympics
